      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:59:14",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/59/1278",
      "text": [
        "مَا بَيْنَ اَلْمَنْزِلَيْنِ وَ أَتَمَّا فِي اَلْمَنْزِلَيْنِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1278 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said:\n\"The camel driver (al-Jammal) and the mule driver (al-Mukari) should shorten their prayers while traveling between their stopping places, but when they reach their stopping places, they should offer the complete prayers”."
        ]
      }
    },
